    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PAA\nConquest\nof the Pacific\nNOVEMBER 1935\nPAN AMERICAN'S INAUGURATION OF REGULAR SERVICE - SAN FRAN. TO MANILA\nNOTE: POSTAGE RATE 751 FOR COMPLETE TRIP\nFOLLOWING EARLIER\nSURVEY FLIGHTS AND\nEXTENSIVE PREPARATION\nINCLUDiNG BUiLDING OF\nBASES AT MIDWAY, WAKE,\nGUAM, AND MANILA, PAN\nAM INAUGURATED REGULAR\nSEXVICE TO HONOLULU AND\nPOINTS WEST. AS ON SUR-\nVEY FLIGHTS, ED MUSICK\nCOMMANDED THE FIRST.\nFLIGHT.\nMARTIN M-130\nCHiNA CUPPER OVER GOLDEN GATE ON INAUGURAL\nTRIP",
      "NOV 297\nPM\n1935\nMANILA\nTRADE CENTER\nOF THE\nPACIFIO",
